text: Zdenka Procházková (4 April 1926 – 25 August 2021) was a Czech actress. She was known for her role as Helena Fejfarová in the 1949 thriller movie A Dead Man Among the Living. She was married to actor Karel Höger. Procházková was born in Prague.
